
Darkwill – Privacy Policy
Last Updated: [Add Date]
This Privacy Policy explains how Darkwill (“the Bot”, “we”, “our”, “us”) collects, uses, and protects information when you use the Bot inside any Discord server.
By using Darkwill, you agree to the terms described below.

1. Information We Collect
Darkwill collects only the information required for its features to function properly.
The Bot may collect the following types of data:

1.1. Message Content (Optional & Limited)
Message content is only accessed for features that rely on it, such as:
Auto-Responder
Auto-Moderation (anti-link, anti-spam, etc.)
Logging deleted/edited messages
Keyword-based triggers
Message content is NOT stored permanently and is only processed in real time.

1.2. Discord User Data
User ID
Username & discriminator
Roles
Server permissions
This data is used only for identifying users for moderation, logging, and automation features.

1.3. Server Data
Server ID
Channel IDs
Role IDs
Server settings & configurations
Ticket system logs (if enabled)
This data is stored only to maintain your server's bot configuration.

2. How We Use Your Data
Darkwill uses collected data only for the following purposes:
Provide security & Anti-Nuke protection
Manage moderation commands
Process auto-moderation events
Operate logging systems
Manage Ticket, Welcomer, and Utility features
Save server configurations
Improve bot performance and stability
We do not use your data for advertising, analytics, profiling, or AI training.

3. Data Storage & Retention
Darkwill stores only necessary configuration data (server settings, automod settings, ticket system settings, etc.).
Message content is not stored and is removed immediately after processing.
Logs (delete/edit messages, joins, bans, etc.) may be temporarily cached depending on server settings.
You can request deletion of your server data at any time.

4. Data Sharing

We do not share, sell, or trade any collected data to third parties.
Data is only processed internally for bot functionality.
We may share limited data only if:
Required by Discord’s security requirements
Required by law (rare cases)

5. User Rights
Users and server admins have the right to:
Request deletion of their data
Request the bot to leave a server
Disable features that use message content
Opt-out of auto-moderation tracking
You may request data removal by contacting the bot owner or support server.

6. Opt-Out Policy

Users can opt out of message-based processing by:
Disabling Auto-Responder
Turning off specific logging modules
Turning off Auto-Moderation features
Removing the bot from the server (full opt-out)

7. Security Measures

We take reasonable measures to protect your data:
Secure database storage
Limited access to configuration data
No unnecessary logging of personal information
No long-term storage of message content

8. Children’s Privacy
Darkwill does not knowingly collect information from users under 13 years old, in accordance with Discord’s Terms of Service.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy if new features require changes.
Any major updates will be announced in the support server.

10. Contact Information
If you have any questions or want to request data removal, you can contact us through:

Owner: raxeyn
Support Server: https://discord.gg/tx38Jxvg9Y
